         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
                 <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> 
                 <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
               <lb n="2"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Samiaria">Samiariae</name>
               <lb n="3"/>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Chrysogone">Chrysogone</name>
                  </persName>
               <lb n="4"/>
                  uxori <choice><sic>k</sic><corr>c</corr></choice>arissim<supplied reason="omitted">ae</supplied>
               <lb n="5"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Cornelius">Cornelius</name>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Philo">Philo</name>
                  </persName>
               <lb n="6"/>
                  maritus et
                  <persName>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Chrysogonus">Chrysogo
               <lb n="7" break="no"/>
                     nus</name>
                  </persName>
                  filius item
                  <persName>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Aphrodite">Aphro
               <lb n="8" break="no"/>  
                        dite</name>
                  </persName>
                  alumnae.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               To the divine spirits. Cornelius Philo, the husband, and Chrysogonus, the son, [made this]
               for the most beloved wife Samiaria Chrysogone, [and] likewise the ward, Aphrodite.
            </p>
         </div>
